Comment:
I love this movie, but...man, Cap lives a LOT of his life in montage.  There's the "struggling at boot camp" montage, the "Cap goes on tour on stage" montage, and the "Cap goes on a tour of duty" montage.  It's like watching "Rocky" three times in rapid succession.  I mean, obviously, they have to cover a long span of time and I'm not sure if there's a better way for them to do it, but it's still kind of hard to ignore.

Also, the "I have to crash the plane" bit felt like kind of a weak ending.

Title: Captain America: The First Avenger - Trailer
Comment:
I have to say, I really liked this movie. It had great acting, superb special effects and action scenes, a memorable musical score and a really well-written script.

I'll admit right now though that I never read the original Captain America comics, so I have no idea whether this is a faithful adaptation or not.

But regardless, I enjoyed watching it.

If nothing else, it's a real breath of fresh air to finally have a superhero movie where the superhero in question ISN'T flawed in some way.
